3 unit Mike’s Hot Honey®
1 unit Demi-Baguette
4 ounce Mozzarella Cheese
2 ounce Prosciutto
1 tablespoon Olive Oil

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

Slice baguette crosswise into 6 - 8 rounds. Spread slices out on a baking sheet, drizzle with oil, and season with salt and pepper. Toast on top rack of oven until golden brown, 5-10 minutes.

Meanwhile, slice mozzarella into 6 - 8 rounds.

Arrange mozzarella and prosciutto on a serving board. Drizzle both with hot honey. Serve with toasted baguettes on the side.